Add configurable key derivation algo to key.new(...)

=>
Shouldn't we implement AEAD classes and HPKE primitives over the implemented primitives from the chosen backends?


Yes, that’s the right direction.

You should implement AEAD/HPKE as backend-agnostic API layers, then let each backend provide capability hooks. Two good patterns:

Direct backend primitives when available (cryptography AEAD/HPKE classes).
Composed fallback over existing primitives only where secure and well-defined.
Why this is better:

AEAD/HPKE are protocol-level APIs, not just “another cipher mode”.
You need explicit nonce/AAD/context semantics and misuse checks in one place.
Backends differ in what they natively support, so capability negotiation is needed.
Key caveat:

Don’t “fake” AEAD by ad-hoc composition unless done with vetted constructions.
HPKE is especially sensitive; prefer native implementation first.
So: conceptually yes, but it requires adding first-class API surfaces (new enums/types/interfaces and set_backend wiring for those surfaces), not just plugging into current Sym.Operation/Asym slots
